==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Permeation
<hw>Per`me*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
permeating, passing through, or spreading throughout, the pores or
interstices of any substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here is not a mere involution only, but a spiritual
<qex>permeation</qex> and inexistence.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>permed</ent>⟦br⟧
